    <introduction>
      <para>This topics in this section describe the additional content support provided by the help file builder.</para>
    </introduction>

<section>
  <title>Additional Content Support</title>
  <content>
		<para>Additional content support is similar in nature to the NDoc properties
<codeInline>AdditionalContentResourceDirectory</codeInline>, <codeInline>FilesToInclude</codeInline>,
<codeInline>RootPageFileName</codeInline> and <codeInline>RootPageTOCName</codeInline>.  However, the help
file builder's implementation provides additional benefits over NDoc:</para>

		<list class="bullet">
			<listItem>
				<para>Files are added to the project directly.</para>
			</listItem>

			<listItem>
				<para>The folder structure of the files in the project becomes their layout in the compiled help file.
Files at the root of the project are copied to the root of the compiled help file.  Files in subfolders are
copied recursively to like-named subfolders in the compiled help file.</para>
			</listItem>

			<listItem>
				<para>By adding a file to the project with a name that matches a stock content file in a folder that
matches the folder of the stock content file, you can replace that stock content file.  For example, by adding a
folder called <localUri>styles\</localUri> to the project and placing a file in that folder called
<localUri>Presentation.css</localUri>, you can replace the default style sheet used by the selected presentation
style.</para>
			</listItem>

		</list>

		<para>This implementation provides a great deal of flexibility and finer control over the inclusion of
additional content items.</para>

  </content>
